name: Argentina vs Peru
summary: Argentina secured their place in the Copa America quarterfinals with a 2-0 victory over Peru. Lautaro Martinez scored both goals for Argentina, who advanced to the knockout stage as Group A winners. The match was played without Lionel Messi, who was rested for the game. Argentina dominated the match from the start and created several chances, but it wasn't until the 43rd minute that Lautaro Martinez gave them the lead. He scored a second goal in the 84th minute to seal the victory. Peru had a few chances to score, but they couldn't find the back of the net. The result means that Argentina will face Ecuador in the quarterfinals, while Peru is eliminated from the tournament.
